\title{Evaluation of expressions of the addition language}

\p{Evaluation under the [small-step semantics](plt-languages-0006) for the addition
language consists of zero or more transition steps. Formally, this is captured by taking
the reflexitive transitive closure of the transition relation, written
#{{\overset{*}{\rightarrow}}}. The evaluation of #{e} to #{e'} may be writen

##{e \overset{*}{ \rightarrow } e' = e \rightarrow e_1 \rightarrow \ldots \rightarrow e_n \rightarrow e'}}
